    "• Statement-level and category-level instructions achieve better performance in each metric.",
    "This is because they are very brief, fluent, and close to real-world scenarios.",
    "However, our dataset contains only 36 categories, and only using these instructions as training data may lack diversity.",
    "• Overall, this human evaluation confirms that the coarse instructions generated by the multigranularity instruction mechanism are not only fluent and relevant to the task, but also more aligned with real world scenarios.",
    "They are an important supplement to the original hybrid-level instructions."
